Rating: 4
This was absolutely fantastic. Per a reviewer's suggestion, I skipped the crust and added the cheesecake filling to decorative chocolate cups which I got from the bakery section of my supermarket and chilled them for the suggested 3 hours. The filling was surprisingly delicious, with such intense vanilla flavor which I added due to the Vanilla vodka I used. It turned out light and creamy like a mousse. I also doused the berries with the vanilla vodka and the result was heavenly. The best part is, it came together in a flash. This will be in my regular rotation from now on. Superb.

