Timesaver: you can save a step on the berries by using vanilla vodka. (Stolichnaya Vanil is a favorite of ours.)

Rating: 4
This is a great recipe. I have made it a few dozen times over the last few years and it's always popular. I make it in a full-size tart pan instead of individual tart pans (which works out great) but the filling can also be piped into miniature chocolate dessert cups to serve crowds. Also, for the berry sauce, just grab a bag of frozen mixed berries and heat them on the stove (you don't need to add anything).There was a point, actually, where my father-in-law wouldn't let me into the house without this cheesecake in hand. We ate it a lot that summer.

