Rating: 3
I've made a lot of cheesecakes in the past and the fact that these tartlets did not require baking led me to believe that they would not have 'authentic' cheesecake character. But they turned out very nicely. I have to say that if it wasn't for the vanilla-vodka berry topping, this dessert would not have been nearly as delicious. That berry mixture made all the difference. This is a simple, tasty dessert with lots of visual appeal.

Rating: 4
This recipe is OUTSTANDING!! The cheesecake is absolutely dreamy, and the vodka-vanilla-berry mixture is pure heaven. It would be wonderful over pound cake or ice cream. Yum! Overall, this is one of the absolute best cheesecake desserts I have ever eaten and/or made. Be careful about the crust, though. It was probably my oven, but I baked it for the recommended time and it came out a bit crisper than I would have liked.

